==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] [[Έλλην]] (''Ellen'') "Greek", "luminary", from prefix [[έλ-]] (''el'') "bright, shiny". (See ''[[helios]]'' "sun", [[electron]] "amber", etc.). In Greek mythology [[Έλλην]] was the son of [[Δευκαλίων]] and [[Πύρρα]], whom the [[Έλληνες]] (''Hellenes'') "Greeks", were named after.

===Noun===
An inhabitant, resident, or a person of descent from [[Hellas]], "Greece".